headline.main: Ireland to Raise Up to 1.25 Billion Euros in Dual Bond Auction
headline.print_headline: Ireland to Raise Up to 1.25 Billion Euros in Dual Bond Auction

lead_paragraph: Ireland will seek to raise up to 1.25 billion euros on Thursday in its second dual bond auction of the year to further replenish the scarce pool of Irish debt eligible for the European Central Bank's bond-buying programme.
